INSERT INTO `wst_posts` VALUES("683", "3", "2016-11-27 14:55:02", "2016-11-27 14:55:02", "<strong>Most admired personal trainer in town</strong>\r\n\r\nRons career as a personal trainer was nothing less of a fairy tale. Over the years, his excellent training skills and resources had helped establish a reputable business. Women trooped to his center in masses. As a matter of fact, from a point where he had to dish out flyers begging people to attend his gym, Ron had transitioned to a point where interested clients had to submit applications for consideration. In his hometown, Ron has helped many women to gain fitness and lose weight. Oblivious of the challenges that could face his business, Ron purely focused on making money and satisfying his ever growing customer base not realizing the importance a personal trainer insurance . To match his growing success, Ron laid plans that would see him not only expand his facility but also open new branches across his hometown and beyond. It always hurt him to have to turn away clients due to resource limitations and as such, he set out to save with an aim of opening more branches. Quite a vision, one would say. Little did Ron know that tragedy could strike at any time and hence saw no need to take a personal trainer insurance.\r\n\r\n<strong>That day at gym that Ron will never forget</strong>\r\n\r\nOn this fateful day, all started well for Ron. As usual. He woke up early morning to attend to his morning batch of clients. Things went quite well and the morning batch of clients left for work. Often, the morning batch was comprised of the working class client that had some experience in working out. However, the second batch attracted some novices as well. Well, as Ron was busy training this lot at the gym, tragedy struck. One of the new ladies that had just started training slipped and due to her inexperience, broke her leg. Conventionally, Ron should have been there to guide her but due to a large number of clients, he was busy with another client at the time. To Rons surprise, the broken leg would result in a 3-year period of disability. What followed was a chain of events that Ron had not anticipated. The lady threatened legal action forcing Ron to seek legal assistance. Surprisingly, the advocate he sought informed him that he was liable as this would count as negligence and as such, his only option was to negotiate with the lady for a settlement. After seeking the advice of several lawyers, Ron realized he had no other choice. How he wished that he had a personal trainer insurance.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-685\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/iStock-478864354.jpg\" alt=\"Young sad woman injured her leg while male coach is helping her.\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1367\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>I paid for the injury. And it was painful</strong>\r\n\r\nEventually, Ron had to pay the lady for the injury. The price was enormous, Ron had to part with a whopping $82,000 wiping out not just his entire savings but also forcing him to seek a loan to cater for the deficit since her savings were not enough to cover everything. All his plans were shattered and rather than focus on expanding, Ron found himself having to focus on repaying the loan. This is when the reality struck Ron, had he had an insurance cover, he would not have had to pay, the insurance company would have paid. However, thanks to his ignorance, Ron found all his plan spoilt and his dream of opening new branches in the near future all shattered. What had seemed as an unnecessary expenditure, suddenly became an important necessity. As old adage would have it, if wishes were horses, all beggars would ride. Ron could only wish that he had insurance cover. Thinking back and imagining how many businesses suffer similar consequences, Ron could not hide his wish that all trainers should have an insurance policy to cater for foreseeable and unforeseeable circumstances. Eventually, with no funds and the resulting heavy debt, Ron had no choice but to wind a business he had worked too hard to build. In a blink, all that Ron had built over the years was over. His career as a personal trainer had met its tragic end. Ron case reflects millions of similar case that occur annually. With a professional liability insurance, Rons case would have been different.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Professional liability insurance could save Rons career</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-686 size-medium alignleft\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/iStock-470950444-300x200.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" />\r\n\r\nThe professional liability insurance or in this case, a personal trainer insurance, covers any financial obligations arising from errors, mistakes, oversights or any damages to individuals or property. With it, you can guarantee that any injury, damage, loss caused to any person or entity, either by you or any other persons acting on behalf of your business are fully covered. Professional liability insurance is based on turnover, workforce, and the activities practiced by the company.\r\n\r\nGuarantee for a local professional or a company should be a reflex when one becomes an entrepreneur. One should immediately think of the damage that may be caused. In addition, it is often mandatory in contracts for which a certificate of insurance is required when you install. But such assurances are not the only ones necessary for the proper functioning of a professional activity. As part of your professional activities, operation of your business, marketing your products or use of, or the services that you will make, you can cause damage to your employees, your customers or a third party. This is why professional liability insurance is essential. This is a blanket security. It allows you to secure the sustainability in light any major risks. Professional liability insurance is the best way to protect yourself against potential risks which could happen by you, that of your employees or that of your professional equipment.\r\n\r\nWithout proper insurance or in Rons case, personal trainer insurance, you may find yourself in a very difficult situation involving a civil offense. You will be ordered to pay you damages that may end up consuming your personal assets. In general, any professional activity is likely to cause damage. Under certain conditions, professional liability may be initiated and penalties imposed. The amounts involved sometimes exceed what people can pay by themselves. Civil liability is a legal obligation that requires anyone to repair damage to a victim occurring as a result of failure in his/her responsibility. If you have a professional liability insurance, the insurance will make such payments on your behalf.", "That one mistake that put an end to Rons career as a promising personal trainer", "", "draft", "open", "open", "", "one-mistake-put-end-rons-career-promising-personal-trainer", "", "", "2016-12-07 23:49:05", "2016-12-07 23:49:05", "", "0", "https://www.next-insurance.com/?p=683", "0", "post", "", "0");
