INSERT INTO `wst_posts` VALUES("688", "3", "2016-11-27 15:20:04", "2016-11-27 15:20:04", "In this advent world today, no one is immune to a lawsuit. As with any profession where you have a client hire you for your expertise such as a personal trainer, you need to be prepared for accidents in case they happen. Personal trainer insurance is essential to protect oneself from any risks that may crop up when training clients in a private home studio or a gym and lead to a lawsuit.\r\n\r\n<strong>When a chill sunny day at park becomes a nightmare</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-690 alignleft\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/iStock-467850843-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"Young fitness man exercising with suspension trainer sling and personal sport trainer in City Park under summer trees\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" />\r\n\r\nHeres every personal trainer\'s nightmare: A lady files a lawsuit against her personal trainer claiming that she incurred an injury, got her knee broken from rigorous training sessions that left her in excruciating pain. The lady files a lawsuit against the trainer for bodily injury and is eligible for claiming compensation for her broken knee during a training session while using a TRX machine. This was due to the trainers negligence, carelessness and recklessness for setting up the TRX machine wrongly before exercise which resulted to the lady incurring a broken knee. In this case if the lady sues for bodily injury using the TRX machine as a result of negligence by the trainer due to: The trainer breached the duty of care and incurred a broken knee, failure to provide a personalized exercise routine as promised and failure to warn the plaintiff about the risks of injury associated with the TRX machine exercise. However, having a personal trainers liability can provide a trainer coverage and protection against such a claim. In this case, the trainer would have to suffer hefty charges and even have his license as a trainer revoked rendering him jobless. Due to the physical nature of the work a personal trainer does, the risk exists that a client can be harmed or can claim to be injured. In some cases, even when you guide physically healthy and fit people clients may have hidden physical health problems that may be aggravated by exercise. With insurance coverage, the trainer would be protected against this claim.\r\n\r\n<strong>The trainer who caused data loss</strong>\r\n\r\nAre you wondering how this could lead to a personal trainer lawsuit?\r\n\r\nDuring a training session, Tina a personal trainer from New York accidentally dropped a weight over her customers iPhone. The customer who was a businesswoman claimed that she had several important presentations that needed to be done and as a result, the data loss resulted in $42K damage. In this case, the customer sue\'s Tina for property damage and is eligible compensation for her iPhone and damages incurred by the loss of data. If Tina is not insured under General Liability insurance and the customers claim is successful, a court could award damages against Tina based on the seriousness of the data loss occurred resulting in very costly charges that may render Tina bankrupt. Thankfully General Limited insurance (explained further below) can prevent this. With General Liability, Tinas policy would protect her from a lawsuit filed against her by the customer claiming that dropping the weights on her iPhone was her fault and she ought to have been more careful. Unfair dont you think? But the court would not rule this case as unfair. Tina would be liable to pay a damage fee named by the court to cover the losses incurred from the data loss and have her replace the iPhone not to mention, the stress, pressure, and financial risks-money she would have to spend to cover the costs of the claims.\r\n\r\n<strong>The fat lady didnt sing this time</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-691 alignleft\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/iStock-618608780-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"Young sporty woman is discussing workout plan, progress and statistics with her fitness instructor using digital tablet.\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" />\r\n\r\nDo you think you could sue your personal trainer for saying mean things about you? Apparently, you can. In this case, James a personal trainer hired several employees to build training programs that fit his customers. One of the customers, Debbie, is an obese young woman who seeks training sessions to cut weight. While training, Debbie overhears David an employee of James talking in an unflattering way about her weight and gets very offended. Instead of letting it go, Debbie then decides to sue James for Personal injury due to Davids inconsiderate words that hurt her feelings claiming compensation. Here James (the personal trainer) is at risk of being held liable for this Personal injury even though he wasnt the directly the one who hurt Debbie and would have to incur the damages ordered by court putting a financial risk on his business. Scary, huh!? I think so. With General liability Insurance coverage James can be covered against this claims hence not risk ruining his or the gyms reputation or incurring huge financial risks in damages ordered by a court of law.\r\n\r\n<strong>So what is General Liability Coverage?</strong>\r\n\r\nSometimes referred to as commercial general Liability (CGL), General Liability Coverage is a personal trainer insurance that protects you and your business and covers the cost of your business from another person or business claims of body injury, associated medical costs and damage to property as a result of you supplying products or you going about your business. Business is intrinsically risky, but having a General Liability Coverage safeguards against many known and unknown risks. The General Liability coverage basically protects you and your business against third party claims. If you are a personal trainer (self-employed) and employ other staff in your business it is critical you consider investing in the General Liability Coverage. From the cases above, if each of the plaintiffs was insured under the General Liability Coverage they all would be safeguarded from all the claims stated against them, up to the limits of their policy. Policies under General Liability Coverage shield you as a personal trainer from litigation, an expense of out-of-court settlements and any judgments awarded by courts. No Fitness instructors and Personal trainers should consider taking the risks to operate a business without General Liability Coverage, it is definitely asking for trouble and putting oneself against huge financial risks to provide important liability protection to cover any unforeseeable risks against yourself and your business. Take your time, research and shop around to find the best policy on the General Liability Coverage that protects you and your business from any risks. For a reasonable sum of money a year, you can have a peace of mind knowing that help is right around the corner. Dont get caught up in a nightmare lawsuit. As the old adage goes, its better to be safe than sorry (especially when your reputation is on the line).", "Why those successful personal trainers lost their jobs?", "", "draft", "open", "open", "", "successful-personal-trainers-lost-jobs", "", "", "2016-12-07 23:33:59", "2016-12-07 23:33:59", "", "0", "https://www.next-insurance.com/?p=688", "0", "post", "", "0");
