INSERT INTO `wst_posts` VALUES("1628", "3", "2017-07-26 03:23:58", "2017-07-26 10:23:58", "Pricing varies per certification and accompanying materials, but most programs fit into the$400-$800 range, including materials.", "How much does it cost to become a personal trainer?", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "much-cost-become-personal-trainer", "", "", "2017-07-26 03:29:19", "2017-07-26 10:29:19", "", "0", "https://www.next-insurance.com/?post_type=hrf_faq&#038;p=1628", "0", "hrf_faq", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wst_posts` VALUES("1629", "3", "2017-07-26 03:27:27", "0000-00-00 00:00:00", "", "Auto Draft", "", "auto-draft", "closed", "closed", "", "", "", "", "2017-07-26 03:27:27", "0000-00-00 00:00:00", "", "0", "https://www.next-insurance.com/?post_type=hrf_faq&p=1629", "0", "hrf_faq", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wst_posts` VALUES("1630", "3", "2017-07-26 03:44:26", "2017-07-26 10:44:26", "It really depends on your existing level of knowledge and experience. In most cases, obtaining personal trainer certification will take between two and four months. In certain cases, such as in conjunction with an academic degree, certification can take a few years.", "How long is the process to become a personal trainer?", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "long-process-become-personal-trainer", "", "", "2017-07-26 03:44:26", "2017-07-26 10:44:26", "", "0", "https://www.next-insurance.com/?post_type=hrf_faq&#038;p=1630", "0", "hrf_faq", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wst_posts` VALUES("1631", "3", "2017-07-26 03:45:10", "2017-07-26 10:45:10", "Personal trainers just starting out earn approximately $38k per year. With a few years experience under their belt, trainers can make upwards of $50k  and this is not counting those who start their own successful gyms.", "How much money do personal trainers make?", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "much-money-personal-trainers-make", "", "", "2017-07-26 03:45:10", "2017-07-26 10:45:10", "", "0", "https://www.next-insurance.com/?post_type=hrf_faq&#038;p=1631", "0", "hrf_faq", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wst_posts` VALUES("1632", "3", "2017-07-26 03:45:31", "2017-07-26 10:45:31", "This is a tough one to answer  certs have their own pros and cons and should be evaluated individually. Having said that, the NASM, ACE, and ISSA certifications seem to be the best known and most popular.", "Which personal trainer certification is the best?", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "personal-trainer-certification-best", "", "", "2017-07-26 03:45:31", "2017-07-26 10:45:31", "", "0", "https://www.next-insurance.com/?post_type=hrf_faq&#038;p=1632", "0", "hrf_faq", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wst_posts` VALUES("1633", "3", "2017-07-26 03:45:50", "2017-07-26 10:45:50", "Almost all certification programs require the applicant to be 18+ and certified in cardiopulmonary resuscitation (CPR) and the use of automatic external defibrillator (AED). In addition, having a high school diploma or GED is required by almost all certifying organizations.", "Are there prerequisites required to become a personal trainer?", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "prerequisites-required-become-personal-trainer", "", "", "2017-07-26 03:45:50", "2017-07-26 10:45:50", "", "0", "https://www.next-insurance.com/?post_type=hrf_faq&#038;p=1633", "0", "hrf_faq", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wst_posts` VALUES("1634", "3", "2017-07-26 03:46:18", "2017-07-26 10:46:18", "Yes. Most gyms require their trainers to show proof of insurance before being hired. Whether working as a gym employee or freelance trainer, being covered is vital against sudden legal issues such as client injury, harmful nutritional advice, or even allegations of sexual impropriety. Not fun, but hey  it happens.", "Do personal trainers need to be insured?", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "personal-trainers-need-insured", "", "", "2017-07-26 03:46:18", "2017-07-26 10:46:18", "", "0", "https://www.next-insurance.com/?post_type=hrf_faq&#038;p=1634", "0", "hrf_faq", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wst_posts` VALUES("1635", "3", "2017-07-26 03:46:55", "2017-07-26 10:46:55", "Material on the exam is standard for each certification, with some variations. In any case, the main subjects youll need to know are basic nervous system functionality, cardiorespiratory essentials, primary muscle movement and contractions, kinesiology, program design, and nutrition.", "What kind of material is on fitness instructor certification exams?", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "kind-material-fitness-instructor-certification-exams", "", "", "2017-07-26 03:46:55", "2017-07-26 10:46:55", "", "0", "https://www.next-insurance.com/?post_type=hrf_faq&#038;p=1635", "0", "hrf_faq", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wst_posts` VALUES("1636", "3", "2017-07-26 03:47:17", "2017-07-26 10:47:17", "Having started out as a gym fitness instructor, you can expand into group training and specialties, and from there, the sky is the limit. Being a CPT can lead to a career in law enforcement, public health, professional sports, or even fitness entrepreneurship like opening your own gym.", "What type of careers can fitness trainer certification lead to?", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "type-careers-can-fitness-trainer-certification-lead", "", "", "2017-07-26 03:47:17", "2017-07-26 10:47:17", "", "0", "https://www.next-insurance.com/?post_type=hrf_faq&#038;p=1636", "0", "hrf_faq", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wst_posts` VALUES("1637", "3", "2017-07-26 03:47:47", "2017-07-26 10:47:47", "Personal trainers must be knowledgeable, trustworthy, friendly, confident, and care deeply about the progress of their clients. Naturally, being in great shape is crucial, and finding the right balance between challenging yet not overworking your clients is the sign of an excellent personal trainer.", "What personal characteristics are important to becoming a trainer?", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "personal-characteristics-important-becoming-trainer", "", "", "2017-07-26 03:47:47", "2017-07-26 10:47:47", "", "0", "https://www.next-insurance.com/?post_type=hrf_faq&#038;p=1637", "0", "hrf_faq", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wst_posts` VALUES("1638", "3", "2017-07-26 03:48:22", "2017-07-26 10:48:22", "Networking is important, especially at the early stages of your personal training career. Many gyms have an announcement board where you can post your availability, and printing up business cards and styled workout gear with your brand logo will help. Be sure to post on the relevant online sites and utilize social media, too. Dont be ashamed to self-promote  but do it tactfully!", "Once Im certified, how do I get clients?", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "im-certified-get-clients", "", "", "2017-07-26 03:48:22", "2017-07-26 10:48:22", "", "0", "https://www.next-insurance.com/?post_type=hrf_faq&#038;p=1638", "0", "hrf_faq", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wst_posts` VALUES("1639", "3", "2017-07-26 03:48:43", "2017-07-26 10:48:43", "Personal training can be a crowded space, so it helps to stand out by earning supplementary certification. Working with children, seniors, or special needs people are great options, as is certification in specific fitness fields such as Pilates, yoga, etc. Its never a bad idea to develop expertise in more fitness fields.", "Do I need to choose a specialty?", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "need-choose-specialty", "", "", "2017-07-26 03:48:43", "2017-07-26 10:48:43", "", "0", "https://www.next-insurance.com/?post_type=hrf_faq&#038;p=1639", "0", "hrf_faq", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wst_posts` VALUES("1640", "3", "2017-07-26 03:49:07", "2017-07-26 10:49:07", "Definitely. Set up a business-oriented Facebook and Twitter account. Post content every couple of days, featuring relevant articles and photos of your training area and clients (with permission). Gym selfies are ok too  but dont overdo it! Social media is also great for promotional campaigns and deal offerings. Plenty of useful guides can be found online to help you plan and execute your social media marketing.", "Should I utilize social media?", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "utilize-social-media", "", "", "2017-07-26 03:49:07", "2017-07-26 10:49:07", "", "0", "https://www.next-insurance.com/?post_type=hrf_faq&#038;p=1640", "0", "hrf_faq", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wst_posts` VALUES("1641", "3", "2017-07-26 03:49:35", "2017-07-26 10:49:35", "Every fitness trainer certification requires recertification of some kind, which makes sense: as a personal trainer, your clients must be reasonably confident in your freshness and knowledgeability. In addition to keeping CPR and AED certification current, trainers are required to gather continuing education credits (CECs), the specifics of which vary for each certification. There is also a recertification fee usually required every two years which ranges broadly from $25-$75, depending on the program.", "Is re-certification required?", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "re-certification-required", "", "", "2017-07-26 03:49:35", "2017-07-26 10:49:35", "", "0", "https://www.next-insurance.com/?post_type=hrf_faq&#038;p=1641", "0", "hrf_faq", "", "0");
